solution: ```class Solution {
public:
    string baseNeg2(int n) {
        if (n == 0) return "0";
        string res;
        while (n) {
            int rem = n % (-2);
            n /= -2;
            if (rem < 0) {
                rem += 2;
                n += 1;
            }
            res.push_back('0' + rem);
        }
        reverse(res.begin(), res.end());
        return res;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n)
space complexity: O(log n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Repeatedly divide n by -2, adjusting remainder to 0/1 and correcting the quotient when remainder is negative. The digits are collected in reverse and reversed at the end.

